Created a file of CCG data from the Diagnostic Atlas of Variation

Structure of the data

The file contains:

  1. Data for 17 CCG maps
  2. Three type of time periods - quarterly, annual and three yearly

This is summarised in table 1.

Table1: Available time periods for each indicator; CCG counts
Period Map 1: Rate of computed axial tomography (CT) activity per weighted population by CCG Map 16: Rate of colonoscopy procedures and flexible sigmoidoscopy procedures per population by CCG Map 17: Rate of computed tomography (CT) colonography procedures per weighted population by CCG Map 19: Rate of gastroscopy (upper gastrointestinal endoscopy) procedures per population by CCG Map 2: Rate of magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) activity per weighted population by CCG Map 20: Percentage of patients undergoing gastroscopy (upper gastrointestinal endoscopy) procedures aged under 55 years by CCG Map 22: Rate of endoscopic ultrasound procedures per population by CCG Map 23: Admission rate for children for upper and/or lower gastro-intestinal endoscopy per population aged 0-17 years by CCG Map 24: Rate of audiology assessments undertaken per weighted population by CCG Map 25: Rate of diagnostic sleep studies undertaken per weighted population by CCG Map 26: Percentage of patients with COPD with a record of FEV1 in the preceding 12 months by CCG Map 27: Rate of urodynamic (pressures and flows) tests undertaken per weighted population by CCG Map 28: Rate of echocardiography activity undertaken per weighted population by CCG Map 29: Rate of peripheral neurophysiology tests undertaken per weighted population by CCG Map 3: Rate of non-obstetric ultrasound activity per weighted population by CCG Map 30: Percentage coverage for initial screening tests for men aged 65 years in the NHS abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) screening programme by CCG Map 36: Percentage of referred babies who had an audiological assessment within four weeks of the decision to refer or by 44 weeks gestational age by CCG
